node.title: Police investigating toddler's suspicious death from injuries
node.description: Police have released the name of a toddler who died with critical injuries after being taken to hospital from a house in Weymouth on Sunday.
node.content:
["Police have released the name of a toddler who died with critical injuries after being taken to hospital from a house in Weymouth on Sunday.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Claire Eastham-Farrelly\n
", "The toddler was Arapera Fia, aged 2.", "Police said the child was taken to Starship hospital, and the death was being investigated as suspicious.", "\"The post-mortem examination confirmed the toddler had multiple serious injuries which are believed to be non-accidental,\" Detective Inspector Warrick Adkin said.", "\"Enquiries at the Weymouth address are continuing and the occupants are currently co-operating.\"", "They said the investigation was in its early stages."]
